vulnerability.name: USN-5887-1
vulnerability.description: Simon Scannell discovered that ClamAV incorrectly handled parsing HFS+ files. A remote attacker could possibly use this issue to cause ClamAV to crash, resulting in a denial of service, or execute arbitrary code. (CVE-2023-20032)  Simon Scannell discovered that ClamAV incorrectly handled parsing DMG files. A remote attacker could possibly use this issue to expose sensitive information. (CVE-2023-20052)

statements.status_notes: Several security issues were fixed in ClamAV.
